"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">stated rationale</a>, which is also a good one, is that =E2=80=9C=
physical users preferred not to have Official Prices which they had been un=
able to trade=E2=80=9D: Because the limit-down prices this week are sort of=
 obviously too high, nobody really wants to buy at those prices, which mean=
s that almost nobody is able to sell at those prices, which means that if y=
ou want to trade nickel at those prices you mostly can=E2=80=99t. The LME o=
pens briefly to perform the mechanics of falling 8%, and then it closes aga=
in; it won=E2=80=99t function as a real exchange until it gets all the way =
back to the real price.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I want to emphasize=
 that I am being too cute here, pretending that the =E2=80=9Creal=E2=80=9D =
price is knowable, and known to be about $30,000 to $35,000. I don=E2=80=99=
t know the real price! In general it is the job of markets to figure out th=
e correct price! In the medium term they are generally pretty good at that,=
 but if you run a financial futures market yes, sure, there will sometimes =
be weird technical dynamics that affect the price from minute to minute, an=
d it will occasionally=C2=A0be plausible to say stuff like =E2=80=9Cthe pri=
ces are becoming disconnected from physical reality.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you run an exchange and you think that, one thing y=
ou could do would be to just say it and do nothing else. =E2=80=9CHey these=
 prices are pretty weird,=E2=80=9D you might say on television, and hopeful=
ly people will hear you and rethink what they=E2=80=99re doing. Some well-c=
apitalized investor will say =E2=80=9Cwow nickel prices are so high that th=
e head of the LME says they=E2=80=99re crazy, I should short some nickel,=
=E2=80=9D and the price comes back down through your sheer moral authority.=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or you could take more drastic action. If =
the prices are weird because people are getting margin calls and being forc=
ed to buy (or sell), you could loosen the margin rules, requiring less marg=
in or giving people more time to pay. (In fact the LME <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27061747.258600/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb2=
