idea if you are=C2=A0<em>quite confident that the prices are wrong=C2=A0</e=
m>and will go back to normal.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or you =
could shut down trading for a bit. This has both of the previous effects: I=
t sends a strong signal to the market that prices are crazy, which will att=
ract well-capitalized investors to take the other side and bring them back =
to normal, and it also gives less-well-capitalized investors some time to l=
ine up more funding so they are not forced to trade at crazy prices. This i=
